       if ({shift_reg[3], shift_reg[2], shift_reg[1], shift_reg[0]} == 4\'b1101) begin\\n                    next_state = SHIFT;\\n                end\\n            end\\n\\n            SHIFT: begin\\n                // Assert shift_ena for 4 cycles\\n                shift_ena = 1\'b1;\\n                next_state = COUNTING;\\n            end\\n\\n            COUNTING: begin\\n                // Assert counting\\n                counting = 1\'b1;\\n                // Wait for done_counting\\n                if (done_counting)\\n                    next_state = DONE;\\n            end\\n\\n            DONE: begin\\n                // Assert done\\n                done = 1\'b1;\\n                // Wait for ack\\n                if (ack)\\n                    next_state = IDLE;\\n            end\\n        endcase\\n    end"}}}')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='\nOutput after running given action:\n<action_output>\n{\n    "is_action_executed": false,\n    "is_syntax_pass": true,\n    "is_sim_pass": false,\n    "error_msg": "{\\n    \\"stdout\\": \\"VCD info: dumpfile wave.vcd opened for output.\\\\nFIRST MISMATCH AT TIME 90:\\\\nInput signals: clk=0 reset=0 data=x done_counting=x ack=x\\\\nOutput signals: shift_ena=0 counting=0 done=0\\\\nExpected signals: shift_ena=1 counting=0 done=0\\\\nHint: Your FSM didn\'t pass the sample timing diagram posted with the problem statement. Perhaps try debugging that?\\\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob151_review2015_fsm/tb.sv:74: $finish called at 25346 (1ps)\\\\nHint: Output \'shift_ena\' has 208 mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time 90.\\\\nHint: Output \'counting\' has 336 mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time 110.\\\\nHint: Output \'done\' has 196 mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time 6850.\\\\nHint: Total mismatched samples is 456 out of 5069 samples\\\\n\\\\nSimulation finished at 25346 ps\\\\nMismatch